The paper deals with the detection of Android malware using machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of machine learning algorithms for classification also suggests that it could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the development of a composite classification model, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of real malware samples and benign applications suggests that it could be categorized under networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
